# Nuxt auto-imports

This project uses [Nuxt auto-imports](https://nuxt.com/docs/guide/concepts/auto-imports). Do **not** add manual `import` statements for symbols that Nuxt already provides.

## Use directly (no import)

| Source | Examples |
|--------|----------|
| `app/components/` | `<CatalogDropdownSelect>`, `<OperationalRescueRequestStepsQuoteStep>` |
| `app/composables/` | `useCatalogDropdown()`, `useRescueSupplierSearch()` |
| `app/utils/` | `computeQuoteSummary()`, `getWizardStepKind()`, `formatQuoteMoney()` |
| Vue / Nuxt | `ref`, `computed`, `watch`, `$fetch`, `useToast`, `navigateTo` |

```vue
<!-- BAD -->
import { computeQuoteSummary } from '~/utils/quote-pricing';
import { useCatalogDropdown } from '~/composables/useCatalogDropdown';

<!-- GOOD -->
const summary = computeQuoteSummary(state.quote_lines);
```

```vue
<!-- GOOD — auto-imported component -->
<CatalogDropdownSelect
  v-model="line.service_id"
  :fetcher="fetchServiceDropdown"
/>
```

## Still import explicitly

- Types and interfaces: `~/interfaces/**`, `import type { ... }`
- Zod schemas: `~/schemas/**`
- Constants: `~/constants/**`
- npm packages: `zod`, `vue3-google-map`, `@pinia/colada`, etc.
- Types exported from composables when typing props (e.g. `import type { CatalogDropdownFetcher } from '~/composables/useCatalogDropdown'`)

```ts
// GOOD
import type { RescueRequestFormState } from '~/schemas/rescue-create';
import { z } from 'zod';
```

## When editing files

- Do not add redundant imports for components, composables, or utils.
- If you touch existing manual imports from `~/components`, `~/composables`, or `~/utils`, remove them when safe (no broad refactors unless requested).
